# Terms of Use

**Effective date: June 27, 2026**

These Terms of Use ("Terms") govern your access to and use of the website macrobian.science (the "Site") and your purchase of products and digital materials from Macrobian ("Macrobian," "we," "us," or "our"). By accessing the Site or making a purchase, you agree to these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the Site.

## 1. Who may use the Site

You must be at least 18 years old (or the age of majority in your jurisdiction) and able to form a binding contract to purchase from us. By using the Site, you represent that you meet these requirements and that the information you provide is accurate.

## 2. Our products

**Cosmetic products.** Macrobian sells topical cosmetic skincare products, including serums formulated with cosmetic ingredients such as copper peptide (Copper Tripeptide-1, "GHK-Cu"). Our products are **cosmetics intended to be applied topically to improve the appearance of the skin.** They are not drugs.

**No medical or therapeutic claims.** Our products are not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, mitigate, or prevent any disease or medical condition, and are not intended to affect the structure or function of the body in any way that would classify them as a drug. Statements on the Site have not been evaluated by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) or any other regulatory authority. Individual results may vary.

**Use responsibly.** You are responsible for reading the product label, ingredient list, and directions before use, and for performing a patch test if you have sensitive skin or known allergies. Discontinue use and consult a healthcare professional if you experience irritation or an adverse reaction. If you are pregnant, nursing, have a medical condition, or are taking medication, consult a qualified healthcare professional before using any new skincare product.

## 3. Digital products and informational materials

We may offer digital products, such as informational guides or reference materials (collectively, "Digital Products").

**Educational purpose only.** Digital Products and any consultations are provided for **general educational and informational purposes only.** They do not constitute, and are not a substitute for, professional medical, healthcare, pharmaceutical, legal, or other professional advice. Nothing in our Digital Products or consultations is intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any condition, to recommend or prescribe any drug, treatment, or dosing protocol, or to direct you to obtain or use any prescription or controlled substance. You should consult a qualified, licensed professional before acting on any information you receive from us.

**No professional relationship.** Purchasing a Digital Product or consultation does not create a doctor-patient, pharmacist-patient, or other professional relationship between you and Macrobian. You are solely responsible for any decisions you make and any actions you take.

**License.** When you purchase a Digital Product, we grant you a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable license to access and use it for your own personal, non-commercial use. You may not copy, resell, redistribute, publish, or share it without our written permission.

## 4. Consultations

If we offer a consultation, it is a **general educational discussion** about skincare and our products. It is not a medical appointment, does not involve diagnosis or treatment, and does not result in any prescription, medical recommendation, or treatment plan. Consultations are booked through a third-party scheduling provider, and your use of that provider is subject to its own terms.

## 5. Orders, pricing, and payment

All prices are listed in U.S. dollars and are subject to change without notice. We reserve the right to refuse or cancel any order, including if we suspect fraud, an error in pricing or product information, or a violation of these Terms. If we cancel an order you have paid for, we will issue a refund.

Payments are processed by our third-party payment processor, **Stripe.** By submitting a payment, you agree to Stripe's applicable terms and authorize us and Stripe to charge your selected payment method for the total amount of your order, including any applicable taxes and shipping. You represent that you are authorized to use the payment method you provide.

## 6. Shipping and delivery

We ship physical products to the address you provide at checkout. You are responsible for providing an accurate shipping address. Title and risk of loss for physical products pass to you upon our delivery to the carrier. Delivery times are estimates and not guaranteed. Digital Products are delivered electronically; access details are provided after your purchase is confirmed.

## 7. Returns and refunds

**Physical products.** Because our products are personal-care items, we accept returns only for products that are unopened and unused, or that arrive damaged or defective. To request a return or report a problem, contact us at contact@macrobian.science within 14 days of delivery. Approved refunds are issued to the original payment method. We may decline returns of opened or used products for health and safety reasons, except where required by law.

**Digital products.** Because Digital Products are delivered electronically and cannot be returned, **all sales of Digital Products are final and non-refundable** once access has been provided, except where required by law or where the product is defective or inaccessible.

**Consultations.** Booked consultations may be rescheduled or canceled in accordance with the notice requirements communicated at the time of booking.

If you have any problem with an order, please contact us first — we want to resolve issues directly and fairly before you pursue a chargeback.

